ear with us, as supply will be restored as soon as these repairs are concluded. “EKEDC highly regrets any inconveniences caused by this outage,” Idemuda said in a statement. [NAN] Vanguard News Nigeria Eko Electricity Distribution Company Plc (EKEDC) on Tuesday said lack of access to the faulty feeder supplying electricity to some parts of Mushin area of Lagos, was responsible for the prolonged power outage. September 4, 2018 In "News" The Eko Electricity Distribution Company (EKEDC) says it has restored electricity supply to areas where its injection substations and equipment were submerged by flood on July 8. July 18, 2017 In "News" The management of Eko Electricity Distribution Company (EKEDC) on Sunday attributed the power outage being experienced in some parts of Lagos metropolis to the damage of its equipment by flood. July 9, 2017 In "News"